==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|it|en}} {{term|banca|lang=it}} {{term|rotto|rotta|lang=it}}, which refers to an out-of-business bank, having its bench physically broken. When a moneylender in Northern Italy became insolvent, they would break the bench they worked from to signify that they were no longer in business.

